From: Jiaxing Hu <huhuvmb88@outlook.com>
Date: Mon, 7 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: rk3576: NPU power-domain full clocks + BIU reset

The RK3576 NPU0/NPU1 power domains must run every NPU clock (DSU0 + the
CBUF gates, not just HCLK_RKNN_ROOT/ACLK_RKNNx) and pulse the RKNN BIU
reset (SRST_A_RKNNx_BIU) as the domain powers on, or the NPU bus
interface is left uninitialised: reading an NPU register (e.g. the vendor
rknpu ioctl RKNPU_GET_HW_VERSION) then raises an asynchronous SError and
panics. Add the missing clocks + BIU resets to the power-domain nodes;
the genpd reset-cycle patch pulses the resets on power-on.

Signed-off-by: Jiaxing Hu <huhuvmb88@outlook.com>
---
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3576.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3576.dtsi
@@ -1141,14 +1141,22 @@
 						power-domain@RK3576_PD_NPU0 {
 							reg = <RK3576_PD_NPU0>;
 							clocks = <&cru HCLK_RKNN_ROOT>,
-								 <&cru ACLK_RKNN0>;
+								 <&cru ACLK_RKNN0>,
+								 <&cru CLK_RKNN_DSU0>,
+								 <&cru ACLK_RKNN_CBUF>,
+								 <&cru HCLK_RKNN_CBUF>;
+							resets = <&cru SRST_A_RKNN0_BIU>;
 							pm_qos = <&qos_npu_m0>;
 							#power-domain-cells = <0>;
 						};
 						power-domain@RK3576_PD_NPU1 {
 							reg = <RK3576_PD_NPU1>;
 							clocks = <&cru HCLK_RKNN_ROOT>,
-								 <&cru ACLK_RKNN1>;
+								 <&cru ACLK_RKNN1>,
+								 <&cru CLK_RKNN_DSU0>,
+								 <&cru ACLK_RKNN_CBUF>,
+								 <&cru HCLK_RKNN_CBUF>;
+							resets = <&cru SRST_A_RKNN1_BIU>;
 							pm_qos = <&qos_npu_m1>;
 							#power-domain-cells = <0>;
 						};
